WEBVTT

00:01.727 --> 00:04.486
<i> (upbeat jazz music)</i>

00:04.563 --> 00:07.581
<i> (Frank Sinatra's</i>
<i> "Luck Be a Lady")</i>

00:07.733 --> 00:09.416
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

00:09.493 --> 00:13.178
<i> FRANK SINATRA:</i>
<i> ♪ Luck be a lady tonight ♪</i>

00:13.330 --> 00:16.181
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

00:16.258 --> 00:19.518
<i> ♪ Luck be a lady tonight ♪</i>

00:19.595 --> 00:22.079
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

00:22.097 --> 00:23.689
Two to one? They'll make it.

00:26.527 --> 00:27.443
I'll take that bet.

00:28.729 --> 00:30.754
(cheers and applause)

00:30.773 --> 00:32.197
They look happy.

00:32.274 --> 00:33.615
They all do in the beginning.

00:44.027 --> 00:46.528
Don't throw that.
That's good gum.

00:46.547 --> 00:48.047
All right!

00:48.123 --> 00:49.956
I gotta--I gotta get a shot.

00:50.109 --> 00:51.592
It's Lady Luck.

00:53.112 --> 00:54.386
Okay, get in here with me.

00:54.463 --> 00:56.555
(giggling)

00:59.543 --> 01:01.060
(both laugh)

01:01.211 --> 01:02.877
-Okay.
-Let's finish up and go home.

01:02.897 --> 01:04.563
Don't have to ask me twice.

01:12.722 --> 01:14.055
Oh, come on.

01:14.133 --> 01:16.133
-What are you doing, Stevie?
-(Stevie scoffs)

01:16.135 --> 01:17.910
Can't I have fun too?

01:17.986 --> 01:19.653
I saw you and your sister
fooling around--

01:19.729 --> 01:20.621
Sister-in-law.

01:21.731 --> 01:23.307
I'm married to her brother.

01:23.325 --> 01:25.325
-Hmm.
-Now, if you'll excuse me...

01:25.402 --> 01:27.994
STEVIE: Hey, you interested
in waiting tables downstairs?

01:28.147 --> 01:29.755
I could make that happen
for you, Thony.

01:29.832 --> 01:31.164
Fiona said
you don't allow that.

01:31.317 --> 01:33.467
I mean, not for illegals,
but for you...

01:34.762 --> 01:35.743
No, thanks. I'm fine.

01:35.763 --> 01:36.929
Oh, come on.

01:37.080 --> 01:38.222
Just trying to help out.

01:41.009 --> 01:42.917
You too good for it?

01:42.937 --> 01:44.103
I don't need that kind of help.

01:45.681 --> 01:47.514
Let go of me now.

01:47.666 --> 01:50.592
You think you're so smart?
One phone call.

01:50.644 --> 01:54.020
You won't make that call
because hiring us is illegal.

01:54.173 --> 01:57.174
And turning us in
will only hurt yourself.

01:57.176 --> 01:58.817
Hey, who the hell do you think
you're talking to, huh?

01:58.969 --> 02:01.678
Don't touch me.
I said get off me!

02:01.697 --> 02:02.621
Let go of her!

02:02.698 --> 02:05.699
<i> (tense music)</i>

02:05.775 --> 02:07.793
(Stevie gasping)

02:07.944 --> 02:09.128
I--I--

02:09.964 --> 02:11.463
THONY:
He's not breathing.

02:15.285 --> 02:17.177
FIONA:
Oh, no, no, no!

02:20.366 --> 02:22.457
EMPLOYEE:
Oh, my God. What is she doing?

02:22.476 --> 02:29.356
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

02:36.565 --> 02:38.532
(inhales sharply)

02:40.661 --> 02:41.976
Call 911.

02:41.996 --> 02:43.495
How'd you know how to do that?

02:43.572 --> 02:44.663
She's a doctor.

02:46.725 --> 02:47.624
Let's get out of here.

02:51.321 --> 02:52.671
-Are--are you okay?
-FIONA: Yeah.

02:52.748 --> 02:54.080
Is he gonna be okay?

02:54.233 --> 02:56.324
I don't think he'll ever
be okay, but he'll live.

02:56.343 --> 03:00.921
He's like every other jackass,
but you--you were amazing.

03:01.073 --> 03:02.406
I mean, seeing you do that,

03:02.408 --> 03:04.683
you should be saving lives,
not scrubbing toilets.

03:04.834 --> 03:06.092
Ah, but why choose?

03:06.169 --> 03:09.188
I can save lives
while scrubbing toilets.

03:11.099 --> 03:12.340
<i> IBARRA:</i>
<i> ♪ Island woman rise ♪</i>

03:12.359 --> 03:14.676
<i> ♪</i> Walang makakatigil<i> ♪</i>

03:14.695 --> 03:17.421
<i> ♪ Brown, brown woman, rise,</i>
alamin ang 'yong ugat<i> ♪</i>

03:17.423 --> 03:19.865
<i> ♪ They got nothin' on us ♪</i>

03:20.016 --> 03:22.117
-(walkie talkie squawks)
-What's up, Jaz?

03:24.947 --> 03:27.597
Jaz, Jaz, the eagle has landed.

03:27.599 --> 03:29.357
Copy.

03:29.435 --> 03:31.952
Oy, what are you doing
out here, huh?

03:32.104 --> 03:33.879
-It's past 2:00 a.m.
-I couldn't sleep, Mom.

03:34.030 --> 03:35.105
Where's Chris?

03:35.123 --> 03:36.122
He was supposed to be
watching you.

03:36.275 --> 03:37.633
Luca's watching me?

03:39.795 --> 03:41.327
(gasps)

03:41.480 --> 03:43.305
(walkie-talkie squawks)
I saw you.

03:44.132 --> 03:47.559
FIONA:
Chris. Chris!

03:47.711 --> 03:48.644
Where are you?

03:51.957 --> 03:54.441
You. Get to bed. Now!

03:55.402 --> 03:57.294
It's karma
from when I was a kid.

03:57.296 --> 03:59.655
They're angels compared to you.

04:02.468 --> 04:04.576
-CHRIS: What?
-Chris!

04:04.653 --> 04:05.786
What the hell do you think
you're doing

04:05.821 --> 04:07.471
leaving your sister alone
outside, huh?

04:07.489 --> 04:08.413
She's fine.

04:08.640 --> 04:10.307
Oh, till someone calls
Child Services

04:10.325 --> 04:11.750
and they deport my ass,
and then what?

04:11.827 --> 04:13.067
<i> If you did your homework,</i>

04:13.087 --> 04:14.402
<i> maybe you'd get some sense</i>
<i> into your head.</i>

04:14.421 --> 04:15.662
Whatever.

04:15.739 --> 04:18.590
No--don't "whatever" me!

04:20.761 --> 04:21.677
(groans)

04:23.097 --> 04:24.654
Good night, Thony.

04:24.673 --> 04:26.765
Good night, Fi.

04:26.916 --> 04:29.584
<i> (soft piano music)</i>

04:29.661 --> 04:36.400
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

04:53.961 --> 04:55.335
Luca.

04:57.113 --> 05:00.281
I told you not to wait up
for me.

05:00.359 --> 05:02.634
And no playing video games
this late.

05:02.711 --> 05:04.303
I'm not. It's Daddy.

05:04.379 --> 05:07.789
I told him I was watching Jaz
play ball.

05:07.866 --> 05:09.808
<i> When you gonna come home</i>
<i> to play with your pops, huh?</i>

05:09.885 --> 05:11.143
Marco?

05:12.204 --> 05:13.370
<i> All right, you heard your mom.</i>

05:13.388 --> 05:15.689
<i> Put her on and get to sleep,</i>
<i> okay?</i>

05:16.984 --> 05:18.466
<i> Ball is life.</i>

05:18.544 --> 05:20.301
Ball's life.

05:20.379 --> 05:21.403
<i> MARCO:</i>
<i> Fist bump, Luca.</i>

05:22.214 --> 05:24.072
<i> -(laughs)</i>
-Okay.

05:26.309 --> 05:28.810
<i> Wow, where have you been?</i>
<i> I've been trying to reach you.</i>

05:28.829 --> 05:29.828
I'm working nights, Marco.

05:29.979 --> 05:31.555
<i> When you should be home.</i>

05:31.557 --> 05:33.239
<i> You've been there a year now</i>
<i> since that donor backed out.</i>

05:33.392 --> 05:36.242
-Eight months.
<i> -So what's changed, huh?</i>

05:36.319 --> 05:37.985
<i> Those clinics</i>
<i> still won't see Luca.</i>

05:38.005 --> 05:39.671
We're on a donor registry,
Marco.

05:39.748 --> 05:41.131
We just have to be patient.

05:41.991 --> 05:43.324
Talk about it later.

05:43.344 --> 05:45.585
<i> -Paalam.</i>
<i> -MARCO:</i> Ingat.

05:45.737 --> 05:46.678
(tablet chimes)

05:46.830 --> 05:48.597
Okay, peanut.

05:49.850 --> 05:51.683
Time for blastoff?

05:51.835 --> 05:53.668
Like Neil Armstrong.

05:53.687 --> 05:55.912
LUCA:
And Chino Roque.

05:55.931 --> 05:58.231
Okay, where do you
wanna go first?

05:59.101 --> 06:01.101
Mars--no, Saturn.

06:01.177 --> 06:02.677
-Saturn?
-Yeah.

06:02.696 --> 06:04.345
This one?

06:04.423 --> 06:05.179
Okay.

06:05.199 --> 06:06.848
'Cause it has a ring.

06:06.867 --> 06:09.701
Okay. Now close your eyes.

06:09.853 --> 06:11.328
Close your eyes.

06:12.188 --> 06:13.497
(whispering)
And go to sleep.

06:15.542 --> 06:17.125
<i>♪ Weightless ♪</i>

06:18.695 --> 06:20.212
And free.

06:23.366 --> 06:25.366
Well, he's got a rare
immune deficiency,

06:25.386 --> 06:28.278
and there are no bone marrow
registries back home.

06:28.280 --> 06:30.371
My son is Cambodian-Filipino,

06:30.449 --> 06:32.707
so it's nearly impossible
to find another match.

06:33.619 --> 06:36.686
Yeah, that's why UCLA
referred us to your clinic.

06:38.899 --> 06:40.148
Yes, that's my number.

06:41.735 --> 06:42.809
Thank you.

06:42.961 --> 06:44.385
-(phone beeps)
-Damn it.

06:44.463 --> 06:46.129
What will you do
if they don't call back?

06:46.131 --> 06:48.198
I'll kick down their doors
if I have to.

06:48.909 --> 06:50.725
Elena. Gracias, hey.

06:50.744 --> 06:52.652
Nada for you or you.

06:52.729 --> 06:53.895
You're both fired.

06:53.914 --> 06:54.821
Wait, what?

06:54.973 --> 06:56.306
You can't do that.

06:56.308 --> 06:58.250
I lost my biggest
catering contract

06:58.326 --> 06:59.251
because of that stunt
you pulled.

06:59.402 --> 07:01.086
Yeah, but Thony
saved Stevie's life.

07:01.163 --> 07:02.479
After you nearly killed him.

07:02.497 --> 07:04.756
I told you some of the jobs
can be tricky.

07:04.833 --> 07:06.407
You mean rapey.

07:07.152 --> 07:08.485
Okay, we've worked
three nights with Stevie

07:08.503 --> 07:10.745
since you sent us on that job;
you owe us.

07:10.822 --> 07:13.156
You think you're gonna get paid
for that now?

07:13.175 --> 07:15.158
Yes--unless you want us
to spread the word

07:15.177 --> 07:16.417
that you don't pay.

07:16.495 --> 07:17.844
You're gonna give us
what we're owed

07:17.996 --> 07:19.771
because if we all walk,

07:19.848 --> 07:21.565
you lose more than
one contract.

07:24.928 --> 07:26.778
You know what?

07:26.930 --> 07:28.947
The both of you are trouble.

07:29.098 --> 07:30.356
No more shifts together.

07:30.509 --> 07:32.266
<i> OLLY ANNA:</i>
<i> ♪ Yeah, we still gonna pop ♪</i>

07:32.286 --> 07:34.453
<i> ♪ Comin' in hot</i>
<i> with our swag on flat ♪</i>

07:34.604 --> 07:36.621
<i> ♪ We got hard,</i>
<i> never need no rest ♪</i>

07:36.698 --> 07:39.699
<i> ♪ Ain't no runnin' out,</i>
<i> got the heat on deck ♪</i>

07:39.851 --> 07:42.461
(crowd cheering)

07:52.531 --> 07:53.805
Hey, Thony.

07:53.882 --> 07:55.031
Check it out.

07:55.050 --> 07:57.217
For Shelby's sweet 16.

07:57.293 --> 07:59.269
Your daughter's gonna love it,
Theo.

08:00.981 --> 08:03.648
Arman, man of the hour.
Good to see you, my man.

08:03.725 --> 08:05.542
Good to see you too, Theo.
Everything set to go?

08:05.544 --> 08:08.211
Ah, it's gonna happen just like
you want it to happen.

08:08.230 --> 08:10.213
Cool. Let's get a drink.
I'm parched.

08:10.232 --> 08:12.232
Hey, hey, what the hell's
the matter with you, man?

08:12.308 --> 08:13.825
-Come on, show some respect.
-What?

08:13.977 --> 08:15.385
I know your father
didn't raise you

08:15.387 --> 08:16.978
to act like that.
You need to apologize.

08:16.997 --> 08:18.813
It's okay. He didn't see me.

08:18.832 --> 08:20.499
Anyone who can't
see you is blind.

08:20.575 --> 08:23.576
-Come on, apologize.
-TARIK: All right.

08:23.729 --> 08:26.246
I'm sorry, okay?

08:26.398 --> 08:28.548
-You all right?
-It's fine.

08:31.069 --> 08:32.177
Let's go grab that drink.

08:32.328 --> 08:33.178
-Yeah, okay.
-ARMAN: Make some big money.

08:33.329 --> 08:35.222
-All right.
-Yeah, okay.

08:41.930 --> 08:43.429
<i> DIVA:</i>
<i> I said no.</i>

08:43.582 --> 08:44.430
<i> Come on.</i>

08:44.525 --> 08:46.082
You asking me
to throw the fight?

08:46.101 --> 08:47.600
Screw that noise!

08:47.753 --> 08:50.086
Hey, I'm not asking. Diva!

08:50.105 --> 08:51.938
DIVA: Hell no.
(sighs)

08:52.015 --> 08:54.107
I've worked my ass off
for this, Theo.

08:54.259 --> 08:55.659
Hey, this ain't about you.

08:57.262 --> 08:59.429
Look, I got my family.
My baby girl.

08:59.447 --> 09:02.415
This--this--this is bigger
than all of us.

09:04.193 --> 09:05.502
You make it look good...

09:06.955 --> 09:08.338
And go down hard.

09:21.119 --> 09:23.144
They always think they own us.

09:24.565 --> 09:25.689
Only if we let them.

09:30.629 --> 09:33.238
<i> (dramatic music)</i>

09:33.315 --> 09:39.619
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

09:59.766 --> 10:00.748
(yells)

10:00.767 --> 10:07.564
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

10:20.862 --> 10:23.847
(cheers and applause)

10:23.865 --> 10:30.295
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

10:42.643 --> 10:45.310
(phone ringing)

10:45.387 --> 10:46.127
Hi, sis.

10:46.204 --> 10:47.979
Hey. How was the fight?

10:48.056 --> 10:50.039
If I had bet, I would have won.

10:50.041 --> 10:51.207
May we should get in the ring

10:51.226 --> 10:53.042
because
it would be better than this.

10:53.044 --> 10:54.227
(laughs)
That's right.

10:54.379 --> 10:56.713
Manny Pacquiao, step aside
for Lady Luck!

10:56.731 --> 10:57.572
Well, if I'm Lady Luck,

11:00.068 --> 11:01.159
-PERSON: Whoa, whoa, hey--

11:01.310 --> 11:02.309
TARIK: Hey, yo, Theo,
we're not done here!

11:02.329 --> 11:03.310
ARMAN:
Hey, I'm gonna handle this.

11:03.330 --> 11:04.478
I'm gonna handle this,
all right?

11:04.498 --> 11:05.738
<i> FIONA:</i>
<i> Thony? Thony, are you--</i>

11:05.891 --> 11:07.148
THEO: All right, there was
nothing I could do.

11:07.167 --> 11:09.058
-TARIK: Yo, screw that! You--
-(all shouting)

11:09.077 --> 11:10.410
ARMAN:
I got this. Hey.

11:10.562 --> 11:12.562
we're gonna work
something out, all right?

11:12.580 --> 11:14.005
You gotta keep your cool, man.
All right?

11:14.157 --> 11:15.248
Yeah, no, we're cool.

11:15.324 --> 11:16.582
I swear,
it never happened before.

11:16.659 --> 11:17.509
All right.

11:20.681 --> 11:22.405
<i> (tense music)</i>

11:22.407 --> 11:23.348
ARMAN:
What the hell was that?

11:23.499 --> 11:25.258
TARIK:
I was sick of his excuses.

11:25.334 --> 11:27.001
MATEO:
Oy, no, no, no, no.

11:27.020 --> 11:28.687
(speaking Spanish)

11:30.006 --> 11:31.915
ARMAN: Just get the hell
out of here, man!

11:31.933 --> 11:33.400
Get out of here, now!

11:38.532 --> 11:41.591
(phone ringing)

11:41.593 --> 11:48.415
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

11:56.942 --> 11:58.550
<i> Hola, guapa.</i>

12:23.076 --> 12:24.659
I'm just a cleaning lady.

12:28.081 --> 12:29.414
Let me clean it for you.

12:29.565 --> 12:34.085
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

12:35.088 --> 12:38.314
<i> (dramatic music)</i>

12:38.333 --> 12:43.303
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

12:47.768 --> 12:49.175
<i> (tense music)</i>

12:49.327 --> 12:50.918
If you wait, the blood
will seep in the cement.

12:50.937 --> 12:53.104
It needs to be broken down.

12:54.165 --> 12:55.940
Sodium peroxide is best.

12:56.017 --> 13:01.354
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

13:01.506 --> 13:02.655
What are you?
Some kind of specialist?

13:04.117 --> 13:06.201
I can help you
make this disappear.

13:07.270 --> 13:08.953
Bleach and boiling water
will do it.

13:09.105 --> 13:10.205
Cold water.

13:10.957 --> 13:12.540
Heat sets the stain.

13:14.961 --> 13:16.503
(speaks Spanish)

13:20.634 --> 13:23.384
Just let her do her job.
You might learn something.

13:24.638 --> 13:26.212
(speaks Spanish)

13:26.364 --> 13:32.685
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

14:05.178 --> 14:08.429
(Mateo speaking Spanish)

14:11.017 --> 14:12.267
(Mateo and Arman laugh)

14:14.262 --> 14:16.229
ARMAN: He said he'd
feed his boy off this floor.

14:19.084 --> 14:20.174
I take pride in my work

14:20.193 --> 14:22.318
because I have
a family that needs me.

14:26.032 --> 14:28.441
Would you like a drink?

14:28.593 --> 14:29.242
It's late.

14:30.519 --> 14:33.121
My name's Arman if it makes
any difference.

14:35.542 --> 14:36.766
Where are you from?

14:36.784 --> 14:38.084
Cambodia.

14:39.954 --> 14:41.296
I live in the Philippines.

14:43.550 --> 14:44.632
And I'm going back soon.

14:46.035 --> 14:47.594
I don't need any trouble.

14:52.967 --> 14:55.876
<i> (suspenseful music)</i>

14:55.896 --> 15:02.792
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

15:02.810 --> 15:04.127
(speaking Spanish)

15:04.129 --> 15:06.404
I really need to get back
to my family.

15:13.821 --> 15:17.306
All right, let's get you home
before they miss you too much.

15:17.325 --> 15:24.088
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

15:49.932 --> 15:52.784
<i> (sentimental music)</i>

15:52.860 --> 15:59.666
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

16:40.500 --> 16:43.409
See, this is why my mama
loves you more than me.

16:43.561 --> 16:45.061
Though I don't get
why you'd wanna clean

16:45.079 --> 16:46.587
after cleaning all night.

16:48.174 --> 16:50.842
I don't wanna clean.
I just want things to be clean.

16:50.993 --> 16:53.428
Oh, I know
you're slumming it, doc.

16:56.924 --> 17:00.092
Hey, hey, hey,
what's--what's wrong?

17:00.169 --> 17:02.245
You--you do this
when you're spinning out.

17:02.263 --> 17:04.080
-What--what--what's wrong?
-I need your van.

17:04.098 --> 17:06.607
I'm taking Luca
to the clinic today.

17:07.694 --> 17:10.010
Okay, let--let's talk.

17:10.088 --> 17:11.270
Okay, there's a reason
why most TNTs

17:11.422 --> 17:13.422
won't step foot in a hospital.

17:13.424 --> 17:16.016
If you march in there and you
talk to the wrong person,

17:16.036 --> 17:18.110
you're screwed, okay?

17:18.187 --> 17:20.020
We need to stay invisible.

17:20.040 --> 17:22.040
No, I'm done waiting.

17:22.116 --> 17:24.075
Every day puts Luca at risk.

17:24.227 --> 17:25.376
What if something
happens to me?

17:25.528 --> 17:28.421
If anything happened--
<i> simbako palayo...</i>

17:29.774 --> 17:31.274
Okay, I got Luca.

17:32.034 --> 17:33.700
But if--I mean,
if there's something

17:33.778 --> 17:35.178
you wanna talk about now--

17:42.954 --> 17:44.228
I just need your keys.

17:52.964 --> 17:56.657
Just...don't get pulled over.

18:22.994 --> 18:24.143
There you go, baby.

18:28.942 --> 18:30.108
RECEPTIONIST:
Thony De La Rosa.

18:32.687 --> 18:35.196
I'll be right back, peanut.
Just stay here.

18:35.949 --> 18:37.764
Morning.

18:37.784 --> 18:39.375
So I spoke to Dr. Ramtej
at UCLA,

18:39.377 --> 18:42.678
and he sent me your visa
for a bone marrow transplant.

18:42.697 --> 18:43.621
It's expired.

18:44.791 --> 18:47.183
Well, we--the donor backed out,

18:47.201 --> 18:49.794
and we've been waiting
for another match since then.

